.TH CMT_READ_FILE 3 "CMT" "CMT_READ_FILE" "Read File Function"

.SH NAME
CMT_READ_FILE \- Reads a file into memory and returns its content

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__READ_FILE
.br
.B #include <CMT/CMT.H>

.SH FILES
CMT/FUNCTIONS/READ_FILE.H

.SH DESCRIPTION
Provides functions to read the entire contents of a file into memory.

.TP
.B READ_FILE, read_file()
Reads a file specified by path and returns its content in an
.S s_file
structure.

.TP
.B S_FILE, s_file
Structure returned by
.B READ_FILE
containing the file size and a pointer to the data.

.TP
.B T_FILE, t_file
Typedef for
.B struct s_file

.SH STRUCTURE
.nf
struct s_file {
    size_t size;  // Size of the file in bytes
    char   *data; // Pointer to the file contents
};
.fi

.SH ERROR CODES
0 \- File opened and read successfully
1 \- File does not exist
2 \- Failed to allocate memory for `data` field
3 \- Permission denied while reading file

.SH USAGE
.nf
t_file file_content;
int result = READ_FILE("example.txt", &file_content);
if(result == 0) {
    // use file_content.data
    free(file_content.data); // Always free after use
}
.fi

.SH NOTES
- Always free the `data` field after usage.
- Reads the entire file into memory; not suitable for extremely large files.

.SH SEE ALSO
